# Staging before production (website)

Every user-facing website or API-dependent change must be verified on **staging** before pushing to `main` (live pokepon.org).

## Staging URLs

| What | URL |
|------|-----|
| Staging API | `https://api-staging.pokepon.org` |
| Test any page | `https://pokepon.org/<path>/?api=https://api-staging.pokepon.org` |
| Clear pinned API | `?api=clear` then re-open with staging `?api=` |
| Staging banner | Amber **STAGING** bar at top when API is staging |

**Never** use `http://127.0.0.1:8081` from `https://pokepon.org` (browser blocks mixed content).

## Required workflow

1. Implement changes locally (website repo + bot repo if API changed).
2. **Bot:** deploy to staging only — `bash scripts/deploy-mac-staging.sh` in `~/Developer/Poke-Cards` (not `deploy-mac.sh`).
3. **Verify:** `bash scripts/verify-staging.sh` and manually test the feature with staging `?api=` URL + staging Discord bot sign-in.
4. **Only then** push website to `origin/main` and deploy production bot (`deploy-mac.sh`).

## Do not

- Push website JS/HTML that calls new or changed API endpoints without staging smoke test.
- Change production `pokepon-api-base` meta to `api-staging` on `main` — production meta stays `https://api.pokepon.org`.

Bot staging docs: `~/Developer/Poke-Cards/docs/STAGING.md`.
